{"parentUuid":"514f0b8f-e514-413a-870c-f5b5fecb160b","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/Users/user/Desktop/k3rn","sessionId":"8393077b-fdc2-4c48-8324-5e6d5cc9e329","version":"2.1.62","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"ad2fa2948b958e596","slug":"sequential-bouncing-duckling","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BZtXAAss7dfsPZFiLDKWrX","type":"tool_result","content":"Total tools: 20\n\nTOOL: tools_documentation\n  Description: Get documentation for n8n MCP tools. Call without parameters for quick start guide. Use topic parameter to get documentation for specific tools. Use depth='full' for comprehensive documentation.\n  Parameters:\n    - topic [string] (optional): Tool name (e.g., \"search_nodes\") or \"overview\" for general guide. Leave empty for quick reference.\n    - depth [string] (optional): Level of detail. \"essentials\" (default) for quick reference, \"full\" for comprehensive docs.\n\nTOOL: search_nodes\n  Description: Search n8n nodes by keyword with optional real-world examples. Pass query as string. Example: query=\"webhook\" or query=\"database\". Returns max 20 results. Use includeExamples=true to get top 2 templat\n  Parameters:\n    - query [string] (required): Search terms. Use quotes for exact phrase.\n    - limit [number] (optional): Max results (default 20)\n    - mode [string] (optional): OR=any word, AND=all words, FUZZY=typo-tolerant\n    - includeExamples [boolean] (optional): Include top 2 real-world configuration examples from popular templates (default: false)\n    - source [string] (optional): Filter by node source: all=everything (default), core=n8n base nodes, community=community nodes, ver\n\nTOOL: get_node\n  Description: Get node info with progressive detail levels and multiple modes. Detail: minimal (~200 tokens), standard (~1-2K, default), full (~3-8K). Modes: info (default), docs (markdown documentation), search_pr\n  Parameters:\n    - nodeType [string] (required): Full node type: \"nodes-base.httpRequest\" or \"nodes-langchain.agent\"\n    - detail [string] (optional): Information detail level. standard=essential properties (recommended), full=everything\n    - mode [string] (optional): Operation mode. info=node schema, docs=readable markdown documentation, search_properties=find speci\n    - includeTypeInfo [boolean] (optional): Include type structure metadata (type category, JS type, validation rules). Only applies to mode=inf\n    - includeExamples [boolean] (optional): Include real-world configuration examples from templates. Only applies to mode=info with detail=stan\n    - fromVersion [string] (optional): Source version for compare/breaking/migrations modes (e.g., \"1.0\")\n    - toVersion [string] (optional): Target version for compare mode (e.g., \"2.0\"). Defaults to latest if omitted.\n    - propertyQuery [string] (optional): For mode=search_properties: search term to find properties (e.g., \"auth\", \"header\", \"body\")\n    - maxPropertyResults [number] (optional): For mode=search_properties: max results (default 20)\n\nTOOL: validate_node\n  Description: Validate n8n node configuration. Use mode='full' for comprehensive validation with errors/warnings/suggestions, mode='minimal' for quick required fields check. Example: nodeType=\"nodes-base.slack\", co\n  Parameters:\n    - nodeType [string] (required): Node type as string. Example: \"nodes-base.slack\"\n    - config [object] (required): Configuration as object. For simple nodes use {}. For complex nodes include fields like {resource:\"c\n    - mode [string] (optional): Validation mode. full=comprehensive validation with errors/warnings/suggestions, minimal=quick requi\n    - profile [string] (optional): Profile for mode=full: \"minimal\", \"runtime\", \"ai-friendly\", or \"strict\". Default is \"ai-friendly\"\n\nTOOL: get_template\n  Description: Get template by ID. Use mode to control response size: nodes_only (minimal), structure (nodes+connections), full (complete workflow).\n  Parameters:\n    - templateId [number] (required): The template ID to retrieve\n    - mode [string] (optional): Response detail level. nodes_only: just node list, structure: nodes+connections, full: complete work\n\nTOOL: search_templates\n  Description: Search templates with multiple modes. Use searchMode='keyword' for text search, 'by_nodes' to find templates using specific nodes, 'by_task' for curated task-based templates, 'by_metadata' for filteri\n  Parameters:\n    - searchMode [string] (optional): Search mode. keyword=text search (default), by_nodes=find by node types, by_task=curated task templa\n    - query [string] (optional): For searchMode=keyword: search keyword (e.g., \"chatbot\")\n    - fields [array] (optional): For searchMode=keyword: fields to include in response. Default: all fields.\n    - nodeTypes [array] (optional): For searchMode=by_nodes: array of node types (e.g., [\"n8n-nodes-base.httpRequest\", \"n8n-nodes-base.s\n    - task [string] (optional): For searchMode=by_task: the type of task\n    - category [string] (optional): For searchMode=by_metadata: filter by category (e.g., \"automation\", \"integration\")\n    - complexity [string] (optional): For searchMode=by_metadata: filter by complexity level\n    - maxSetupMinutes [number] (optional): For searchMode=by_metadata: maximum setup time in minutes\n    - minSetupMinutes [number] (optional): For searchMode=by_metadata: minimum setup time in minutes\n    - requiredService [string] (optional): For searchMode=by_metadata: filter by required service (e.g., \"openai\", \"slack\")\n    - targetAudience [string] (optional): For searchMode=by_metadata: filter by target audience (e.g., \"developers\", \"marketers\")\n    - limit [number] (optional): Maximum number of results. Default 20.\n    - offset [number] (optional): Pagination offset. Default 0.\n\nTOOL: validate_workflow\n  Description: Full workflow validation: structure, connections, expressions, AI tools. Returns errors/warnings/fixes. Essential before deploy.\n  Parameters:\n    - workflow [object] (required): The complete workflow JSON to validate. Must include nodes array and connections object.\n    - options [object] (optional): Optional validation settings\n\nTOOL: n8n_create_workflow\n  Description: Create workflow. Requires: name, nodes[], connections{}. Created inactive. Returns workflow with ID.\n  Parameters:\n    - name [string] (required): Workflow name (required)\n    - nodes [array] (required): Array of workflow nodes. Each node must have: id, name, type, typeVersion, position, and parameters\n    - connections [object] (required): Workflow connections object. Keys are source node names (the name field, not id), values define outp\n    - settings [object] (optional): Optional workflow settings (execution order, timezone, error handling)\n\nTOOL: n8n_get_workflow\n  Description: Get workflow by ID with different detail levels. Use mode='full' for complete workflow, 'details' for metadata+stats, 'structure' for nodes/connections only, 'minimal' for id/name/active/tags.\n  Parameters:\n    - id [string] (required): Workflow ID\n    - mode [string] (optional): Detail level: full=complete workflow, details=full+execution stats, structure=nodes/connections topo\n\nTOOL: n8n_update_full_workflow\n  Description: Full workflow update. Requires complete nodes[] and connections{}. For incremental use n8n_update_partial_workflow.\n  Parameters:\n    - id [string] (required): Workflow ID to update\n    - name [string] (optional): New workflow name\n    - nodes [array] (optional): Complete array of workflow nodes (required if modifying workflow structure)\n    - connections [object] (optional): Complete connections object (required if modifying workflow structure)\n    - settings [object] (optional): Workflow settings to update\n\nTOOL: n8n_update_partial_workflow\n  Description: Update workflow incrementally with diff operations. Types: addNode, removeNode, updateNode, moveNode, enable/disableNode, addConnection, removeConnection, updateSettings, updateName, add/removeTag. Se\n  Parameters:\n    - id [string] (required): Workflow ID to update\n    - operations [array] (required): Array of diff operations to apply. Each operation must have a \"type\" field and relevant properties f\n    - validateOnly [boolean] (optional): If true, only validate operations without applying them\n    - continueOnError [boolean] (optional): If true, apply valid operations even if some fail (best-effort mode). Returns applied and failed ope\n\nTOOL: n8n_delete_workflow\n  Description: Permanently delete a workflow. This action cannot be undone.\n  Parameters:\n    - id [string] (required): Workflow ID to delete\n\nTOOL: n8n_list_workflows\n  Description: List workflows (minimal metadata only). Returns id/name/active/dates/tags. Check hasMore/nextCursor for pagination.\n  Parameters:\n    - limit [number] (optional): Number of workflows to return (1-100, default: 100)\n    - cursor [string] (optional): Pagination cursor from previous response\n    - active [boolean] (optional): Filter by active status\n    - tags [array] (optional): Filter by tags (exact match)\n    - projectId [string] (optional): Filter by project ID (enterprise feature)\n    - excludePinnedData [boolean] (optional): Exclude pinned data from response (default: true)\n\nTOOL: n8n_validate_workflow\n  Description: Validate workflow by ID. Checks nodes, connections, expressions. Returns errors/warnings/suggestions.\n  Parameters:\n    - id [string] (required): Workflow ID to validate\n    - options [object] (optional): Validation options\n\nTOOL: n8n_autofix_workflow\n  Description: Automatically fix common workflow validation errors. Preview fixes or apply them. Fixes expression format, typeVersion, error output config, webhook paths.\n  Parameters:\n    - id [string] (required): Workflow ID to fix\n    - applyFixes [boolean] (optional): Apply fixes to workflow (default: false - preview mode)\n    - fixTypes [array] (optional): Types of fixes to apply (default: all)\n    - confidenceThreshold [string] (optional): Minimum confidence level for fixes (default: medium)\n    - maxFixes [number] (optional): Maximum number of fixes to apply (default: 50)\n\nTOOL: n8n_test_workflow\n  Description: Test/trigger workflow execution. Auto-detects trigger type (webhook/form/chat). Supports: webhook (HTTP), form (fields), chat (message). Note: Only workflows with these trigger types can be executed e\n  Parameters:\n    - workflowId [string] (required): Workflow ID to execute (required)\n    - triggerType [string] (optional): Trigger type. Auto-detected if not specified. Workflow must have a matching trigger node.\n    - httpMethod [string] (optional): For webhook: HTTP method (default: from workflow config or POST)\n    - webhookPath [string] (optional): For webhook: override the webhook path\n    - message [string] (optional): For chat: message to send (required for chat triggers)\n    - sessionId [string] (optional): For chat: session ID for conversation continuity\n    - data [object] (optional): Input data/payload for webhook, form fields, or execution data\n    - headers [object] (optional): Custom HTTP headers\n    - timeout [number] (optional): Timeout in ms (default: 120000)\n    - waitForResponse [boolean] (optional): Wait for workflow completion (default: true)\n\nTOOL: n8n_executions\n  Description: Manage workflow executions: get details, list, or delete. Use action='get' with id for execution details, action='list' for listing executions, action='delete' to remove execution record.\n  Parameters:\n    - action [string] (required): Operation: get=get execution details, list=list executions, delete=delete execution\n    - id [string] (optional): Execution ID (required for action=get or action=delete)\n    - mode [string] (optional): For action=get: preview=structure only, summary=2 items (default), filtered=custom, full=all data, e\n    - nodeNames [array] (optional): For action=get with mode=filtered: filter to specific nodes by name\n    - itemsLimit [number] (optional): For action=get with mode=filtered: items per node (0=structure, 2=default, -1=unlimited)\n    - includeInputData [boolean] (optional): For action=get: include input data in addition to output (default: false)\n    - errorItemsLimit [number] (optional): For action=get with mode=error: sample items from upstream node (default: 2, max: 100)\n    - includeStackTrace [boolean] (optional): For action=get with mode=error: include full stack trace (default: false, shows truncated)\n    - includeExecutionPath [boolean] (optional): For action=get with mode=error: include execution path leading to error (default: true)\n    - fetchWorkflow [boolean] (optional): For action=get with mode=error: fetch workflow for accurate upstream detection (default: true)\n    - limit [number] (optional): For action=list: number of executions to return (1-100, default: 100)\n    - cursor [string] (optional): For action=list: pagination cursor from previous response\n    - workflowId [string] (optional): For action=list: filter by workflow ID\n    - projectId [string] (optional): For action=list: filter by project ID (enterprise feature)\n    - status [string] (optional): For action=list: filter by execution status\n    - includeData [boolean] (optional): For action=list: include execution data (default: false)\n\nTOOL: n8n_health_check\n  Description: Check n8n instance health and API connectivity. Use mode='diagnostic' for detailed troubleshooting with env vars and tool status.\n  Parameters:\n    - mode [string] (optional): Mode: \"status\" (default) for quick health check, \"diagnostic\" for detailed debug info including env \n    - verbose [boolean] (optional): Include extra details in diagnostic mode (default: false)\n\nTOOL: n8n_workflow_versions\n  Description: Manage workflow version history, rollback, and cleanup. Six modes:\n- list: Show version history for a workflow\n- get: Get