flow` | Create workflow. Requires: name, nodes[], connections{}. Created inactive. Returns workflow with ID. |\n| 9 | `n8n_get_workflow` | Get workflow by ID with detail levels: full, details, structure, minimal. |\n| 10 | `n8n_update_full_workflow` | Full workflow update. Requires complete nodes[] and connections{}. |\n| 11 | `n8n_update_partial_workflow` | Update workflow incrementally with diff operations: addNode, removeNode, updateNode, moveNode, enable/disableNode, addConnection, removeConnection, updateSettings, updateName, add/removeTag. |\n| 12 | `n8n_delete_workflow` | Permanently delete a workflow. Irreversible. |\n| 13 | `n8n_list_workflows` | List workflows (minimal metadata). Returns id/name/active/dates/tags. Supports pagination via cursor. |\n| 14 | `n8n_validate_workflow` | Validate workflow by ID. Checks nodes, connections, expressions. Returns errors/warnings/suggestions. |\n| 15 | `n8n_autofix_workflow` | Automatically fix common workflow validation errors. Preview fixes or apply them. Fixes expression format, typeVersion, error output config, webhook paths. |\n| 16 | `n8n_test_workflow` | Test/trigger workflow execution. Auto-detects trigger type (webhook/form/chat). |\n| 17 | `n8n_executions` | Manage workflow executions: get details, list, or delete. Actions: get, list, delete. |\n| 18 | `n8n_health_check` | Check n8n instance health and API connectivity. Mode='diagnostic' for detailed troubleshooting. |\n| 19 | `n8n_workflow_versions` | Manage workflow version history, rollback, and cleanup. Modes: list, get, rollback, delete, prune, truncate. |\n| 20 | `n8n_deploy_template` | Deploy a workflow template from n8n.io directly to the instance. Auto-fixes common issues after deployment. |\n\n### Tool Parameters Detail\n\n**`n8n_create_workflow`** — Key tool for creating the 5 new workflows:\n- `name` (string, required)\n- `nodes` (array, required) — each node needs: id, name, type, typeVersion, position, parameters\n- `connections` (object, requi